<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC0FFCCFF26F97B1695C451" box="[238,478,1781,1802]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="720">COPESTYLUM DISPAR</emphasis>
(MACQUART, 1846)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFC0FFCCFF6CF89214D1C241" blockId="23.[164,779,1820,1903]" lastBlockId="23.[826,1441,198,281]" pageId="23" pageNumber="720">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC0FFCCFF6CF8921655C469" box="[164,286,1820,1841]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="720">Puparium:</emphasis>
Posterior breathing tube, shiny and faintly nodulate below TR. Above TR shiny to coriaceous. AP 0.75¥ as long as TR is wide, faintly punctate. Pupal spiracles sharply bent over at halfway point and separated by 1.2¥ the length of a pupal spiracle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36F650CFFC0FFCCFCF2FECD1484C01C" pageId="23" pageNumber="720" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFC0FFCCFCF2FECD13CCC2EC" blockId="23.[826,1441,323,436]" pageId="23" pageNumber="720">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC0FFCCFCF2FECD134BC200" box="[826,1024,323,344]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="720">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
This species may be distinguished from others in the group by the sharply curved pupal spiracles and the faintly punctured AP which is about 0.75¥ as long as TR is wide.
</paragraph>
